{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"timeoutAddSecondsFull"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"priority"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"interval"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSourceFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GDestroyNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The function is called repeatedly until it returns [const"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", at which point the timeout is automatically destroyed and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the function will not be called again."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add"},{"type":"text","text":"], this function operates at whole second"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"granularity. The initial starting point of the timer is determined by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementation and the implementation is expected to group multiple timers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"together so that they fire all at the same time. To allow this grouping, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"},{"type":"text","text":" to the first timer is rounded and can deviate up to one second"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from the specified interval. Subsequent timer iterations will generally run"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the specified interval."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources"},{"type":"text","text":" for details"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want timing more precise than whole seconds, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add"},{"type":"text","text":"] instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The grouping of timers to fire at the same time results in a more power"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and CPU efficient behavior so if your timer is in multiples of seconds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and you donâ€™t require the first timer exactly one second from now, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use of [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add_seconds"},{"type":"text","text":"] is preferred over"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This internally creates a main loop source using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_source_new_seconds"},{"type":"text","text":"] and attaches it to the main loop"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"context using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.attach"},{"type":"text","text":"]. You can do these steps manually"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if you need greater control."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is safe to call this function from any thread."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time. See [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.get_monotonic_time"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timeoutaddsecondsfull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/timeoutAddSecondsFull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets a function t